@NODE "Mail_5" "Re: *ON-TOPIC!* : Rubber-banding"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sat, 31 Jul 1999 08:45:22 -0500
Subject: Re: *ON-TOPIC!* : Rubber-banding
X-UIDL: 36a0fba53294a031a8dd646dcbd3650b

Hi Gaz-JD/FX-s^D

On 31-Jul-99, Gaz-JD/FX-s^D wrote:
> Hi,
>   How would I createa rubber-bading effect on a bitmap (like as seen
> in DPaint, PPaint et al) without destroying the background contents?
> Rubber-banding as in drawing rectangles of variable size (by moving
> the mouse)

The easiest way is to draw the rectangle as "inverted" by using colour -1
for the Line or Wline command.  Then redraw it again, with colour -1 again,
to erase it before updating the size.

I update the rectangle once every VBlank as long as the mousebutton is down
- this makes a nice flicker-free rubber band. 

Later...
-- 
Don't force it, use a bigger hammer.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



