@NODE "Mail_24" "About Window (was: PowerBasic example 2)"
From: Daniel Allsopp <daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 15 Jul 1999 12:14:34 +0100
Subject: About Window (was: PowerBasic example 2)
X-UIDL: 37de582de8b7d8246f847f539dbfa192

Hi Roman,

On 15-Jul-99, you wrote:

> Hi all....
> 
> this is propably a very silly question but can anybody tell me how i can
> create a "about"-window (the one with the ghosted area, the text field and
> the ok button)?

Lots of ways....

req=RTEZRequest(title,body,gadget)

or

req=Request(title,body,gadget)

You make multiple lines on the body by using Chr$(10) i.e

body$=""
body$=body$+"Line 1"+chr$(10)
body$=body$+"Line 2"+chr$(10)
body$=body$="Last Line"+chr$(0)        <- Last line needs chr$(0)

Then

req=Request("About...",body$,"Ok")

req returns the button pressed if you use more than one.

-- 
Cheers,
    Daniel

<tsb>E-Mail: daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk
<tsb>URL: http://www.thesnakepit.demon.co.uk/
<tsb>ICQ Number : 20783863
<tsb>
