Date: Fri, 09 Jul 1999 13:37:23 +0100
Subject: AGA colours
X-UIDL: 5517ed720286bc8d9b18ab1ed07e359b

Hello,

I have come across the following problem:

I open a 256 colour 640x256 screen, using ScreenTags. I get it's bitmap
using ScreensBitmap. I then load a picture into a shape (with help of
ShapesBitmap) and blit it on the first screen. Everything seems to be fine.
Now I'd like to change the RGB components of the sreens palette. And here
the problems begin. I can only get the right colour values if I use Red,
Green and Blue, but when using AGA equivalents, the values aren't right and
the following loop changes colours:

For i=0 To 255
    AGARGB i,AGARed(i),AGAGreen(i),AGABlue(i)
Next i

What am I missing? How can I get the AGA compnents of colours? Should I
specify that when opening the screen or what?

Kind regards
