@NODE "Mail_45" "Re: Amiga DUMP QNX as the OS Partner"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Sat, 10 Jul 1999 18:55:42 +0500
Subject: Re: Amiga DUMP QNX as the OS Partner
X-UIDL: 8f146281cf844deaf55effd1adefcc41

On 10-Jul-99, Sandy Brownlee flashed:
>Hello Scott

>On 10-Jul-99, you wrote:

>> Amiga Int (or what ever thay are now called) have dumped QNX in 
>> favor of Linux as the NG Amiga OS

>And they still intend to get the NG beta released in late Q3?


  Actually, the choice of Linux as a kernal is likely to speed up the
process of getting out the new Amiga OE.  Amiga have allready been
porting parts of the new OE to Linux for months for testing, and the
use of Linux means not having to make hundreds of propriatory new drivers
for the new OE because the manufacturers of the various equiptment are
allready doing that themselves.  There were many good reasons for making
this change, some of which are discussed in Amiga President Jim Collas's
two letters on the subject on www.amiga.de.  I highly recomend going
there and reading them for yourself, as well as his latest Open Letter to
the Amiga Community.
  This all makes beautiful sense, especially in light of the rapid progress
of Linux of late.  I have been studying Linux for allmost 6 years and
have enjoyed my association with the Linux community, who have goals
very like our own in the Amiga community.  Many Amigans are allready
interested in or even actually using Linux and it is growing faster and
better every day.
  Amiga Linux will soon be the best implimentation of any Unix based OS
in the world by vertue of the streamlining which Amiga will bring to it
both software and hardware-wise.
  Like QNX, Linux brings with it great cross-platform and cross-prosessor
capabilities and those are growing very fast.  Unlike QNX, Linux also
brings with it a HUGE crowd of potential Amigans, and GREAT cooperation
by manufacturers.

  Amiga will give Linux a BIG boost, and Linux will give Amiga a BIG boost.

  It's a marriage made in heaven!    YESSSSS!!!



cacha on the flip-flop,

Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



