@NODE "Mail_53" "Re: Amiga DUMP QNX as the OS Partner"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Sun, 11 Jul 1999 23:33:50 +0100
Organization: Pagan Software
Subject: Re: Amiga DUMP QNX as the OS Partner
X-UIDL: 19ffffe964f3589bbb8cee2373e55cf1

I watched as Ashley Scott hammered "Re: Amiga DUMP QNX as the OS Partner"
out on their keyboard...

[SNIP]

> BullShit, I've had this argument for the last couple of days on AFB and
> SD. The linux kernal is pant's! Well QNX and Linux have their pro's and
> con's, 

How, exactly, is Linux pants? It is the *most* stable operating system I've
ever seen.

> but QNX have invested a huge amount of time and money and had
> almost finished the NG Amiga OS.... Then Amiga go and stiff them. I'm
> sorry but QNX is the far superior Kernal and OS. It is very similar in
> design and structure to the The current Amiga's exec...... With the
> advantage of real-time Multitasking ability. 

Nobody knows this for certain, unless you work for QNX.  If you think about
it, all we've seen of the "new OS" is a few dodgy screenshots (and GUI
screenshots aren't exactly hard to fake...trust me, I've made ones myself)
and their word.  And if Amiga decided to dump them, they would have two
choices, (a) slink off and go back to what they were working on and forget
the entire thing or (b) say that they nearly had it finished, publish a few
screenshots and try to get people's support.

> This would make it the
> perfect choice for multimedia aplications, Everyone and there dog is
> making something out of Linux... 

Beacuse it's freeware....which also gives you the amazing additions that the
entire thing can be downloaded, meaning you only have to pay pennies to get
a copy, the vast majority of the software is freeware, bugfixes come out in
hours/days rather than months/years...and what would happen if QNX went
under and took the source code with them?  You may as well bin the
computer, but a Linux system means that the source code can never be
lost....there are simply far too many copies.

> The Amiga needs to be significantly
> different in order to stand out in the crowd! I know the OS or OE if that
> is what you prefer to call it is not going to be a "Out of the box" Linux
> clone... we will have AmigaSoft built over the top of it.... But without a
> good heart in that software it will all go Arse shaped and explode in a
> puff of wind!

Linux *is* a good kernal, the problem is that everyone is getting the OS and
the Kernal confused.  All they've said is that they are going to use a
Linux based kernal, they may still ask QNX to make the rest, we don't know.
 Speculating and complaining will get us nowhere.  Anyone remember the hype
last year when Amiga announced OS4 & OS5? For the best part of a month
people were complaining that the entire thing was going to be an x86
abomination, simply because there are far too many stupid people around who
don't read the details!

I am absoloutly sick to death of people reading the headlines and not the
articles.  And I'm willing to bet that you haven't seen a properly set up
Linux machine either.

But frankly, I couldn't care less what the use.  At the end of the day,
we're only talking about the *kernal*, not the *OS*....so it could
eventually look exactly the same as QNX was going to look....and I really
doubt anyone will be able to tell the difference.

-- 
