@NODE "Mail_79" "Anim Lib"
Sender: parnaudeau@wanadoo.fr
Date: Thu, 29 Jul 1999 08:15:25 +0200
From: Mathias PARNAUDEAU <mathias.p@wanadoo.fr>
Organization: wanadoo.fr
Subject: Anim Lib
X-UIDL: 12ceaf74e4c7cff48b51c51f8886b44d

--------------822C3A3D0FE156D456A1E4A8
Encoding: 7bit

Hi all !

Four or five months ago, I promised you functions (and even a library)
to save
IFF anims from bitmaps, because it was said nothing was existing to do
this.

I know I'm late but I'm very slow ;) Asm is really magic but very hard
debug. I've just found the last big one !! (I hope so)

My lib (called IffYouWantLib) is only 2,5 ko big and allow you to :
   - save a bitmap as an IFF picture (uncompressed)
   - save the first frame (uncompressed too) of an anim
   - add a frame to an anim file with ANIM5 compression.
One palette is saved per frame.

The functions are not optimised at all, but they work, and that's what I
wanted. There are so many changes to do before to get an anim like we
want,
and this is the work of PPaint or MainActor (give only one palette to
the
anim, change frame length, give a better compression, ...).

The syntax is :
   - CSaveIff(#bitmap, filename$, width.w, viewmode.l, #palette)
   - CSaveFirstFrame(#bitmap, filename$, width.w, viewmode.l, #palette)
   - CSaveNextFrame(#bitmap1,#bitmap2,filename$,width.w,#palette)

They are functions and return long word. Width is the bitmap with, and
can be
different of BitMap\Width :-( So, it's important (sometimes).

I chose the lib number 83 beacause it was a free place in the Fred's NCS
list.

I would like to thank Xavier Nuel. And all you to ;)

Remember the second frame is calculated by comparision with the first
one, but
the next frame are compared with the 2-frame-before frame. Maybe not
very
clear ?

I don't have much time to improve this lib but you can send me
suggestions and
others, of course. At the moment I work on my big project called WoW
(available on Aminet in the util/conv directory) : a useful text
converter
(Html, AGuide, Wordworth, Rtf, Ascii, ...).

Cheers,

                  Mathias

-- 
          Mathias PARNAUDEAU - Corto/AFLE

Email    : mathias.p@wanadoo.fr
Site Web : http://perso.wanadoo.fr/supersport/
--------------822C3A3D0FE156D456A1E4A8
