@NODE "Mail_83" "ARexx commands results"
From: Roger Light <rogerlight@mindless.com>
Date: Tue, 20 Jul 1999 21:21:45 +0100
Subject: ARexx commands results
X-UIDL: 41ac1571d187703698ddd9ad0fa0050d

--BOUNDARY.1747980952.1

Hi all,

I have been trying to send an arexx command to ISpell to check to see if a
word exists through Blitz but haven't been having much luck. I have attached
my code and would appreciate it if someone could give me some pointers. I'm
perfectly willing to completely scrap using the blitz arexx commands in
neccesary ;)

On a more specific note, if I use CreateRexxMsg() and specify the host as eg
IRexxSpell, should I then just send commands without "address 'IRexxSpell'"
in?

One more thing - which network do you lot use for IRC? I guess it's not
Arcnet...

Cheers,

Roger
-- 
IRC: oojah | ICQ: 9727627
-------------------
UK University Email Search - Find undergraduate email addresses!
http://start.at/uksearch

--BOUNDARY.1747980952.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="checkword.asc"

spellhost$="IRexxSpell"
;
; ===============================================================
.InitARexx

port.l=CreateMsgPort("CLIENT")
If port.l=0
  Request "Error", "Failed to open msg port","OK"
  End
EndIf

msg.l=CreateRexxMsg(port,"",spellhost$)
If msg.l=0
  Request "Error","Failed to create rexx msg","OK"
  DeleteMsgPort port.l
  End
EndIf

cmd$="QUICKCHECK the"
cmd$="address 'IRexxSpell' "+cmd$

If FindPort_(spellhost$)
 SendRexxCommand msg,cmd$,#RXCOMM|#RXFF_STRING|#RXFF_RESULT
 Wait:While GetMsg_(port) <> msg:Wend ; wait for reply
  If GetRexxResult(msg,1)=0
    If GetRexxResult(msg,2)
      res$=GetResultString(msg)
      Request "Result","Word is "+res$,"OK"
    Else
      Request "Result","No result","OK"
    EndIf
  Else
    Request "Rexx Error",RexxError(GetRexxResult(msg,1)),"OK"
  EndIf
Else
Request "Error","Spell checker not found","OK"
EndIf

DeleteRexxMsg msg.l
DeleteMsgPort port.l

End


--BOUNDARY.1747980952.1

