**********************  Forwarded message  *****************************

I came across some news while surfing the other day, which I feel 
is
important enough to include in this newsletter.  There is currently a
boycott of Yahoo going on, which might be of interest to those of 
you who
own webpages on GEOCITIES.  As you know, Yahoo now owns 
Geocities, and 
apparently they have changed the licencing agreement so that it 
now says
that all content on Geocities sites is PROPERTY OF YAHOO.  
This has
justifiably angered quite a few people.  Makes you proud to be a
MovieThing member though don't it?!  For more info just go to the
following address:
<http://www.sitepowerup.com/boycottyahoo/boycottyahoo.htm>

So I checked out the page and apparently the Terms of Service have been 
changed to say "By submitting Content to any Yahoo property, you 
automatically grant, or warrant that the owner of such Content has
expressly 
granted, Yahoo the royalty-free, perpetual, irrevocable, non-exclusive
and 
fully sublicensable right and license to use, reproduce, modify, adapt, 
publish, translate, create derivative works from, distribute, perform
and 
display such Content (in whole or part) worldwide and/or to incorporate
it in 
other works in any form, media, or technology now known or later 
developed."
 
*********************************************

 Shocking eh? 
   I checked out the Yahoo page and this is correct, and they had a link
which explained that it was only for marketing Yahoo, which is ok if
they did, but the agreement allows them  to do whatever they like if
they wanted!!

