@NODE "Mail_94" "Re: BBS Door Pack with Blitz"
From: Rob Hutchinson <loki@sds.in2home.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 20 Jul 1999 22:36:48 +0100
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: Re: BBS Door Pack with Blitz
Encoding: binary
X-UIDL: eac8dae930cfcec8e43d7892cfb6c438

Hello Bippy
     Hiya, Bippy... ,on 20-Jul-99 you mailed me about: BBS Door Pack with Blitz! So I`ma reply`in...

> Hiya Guys,
> 
> Okay maybe what i'm about to attempt is above my head, but I wanna try..
> So I'll be posting alot of msgs for help over coming weeks!!

Ok no worries.

> Okay basically I run a BBS (Hello Rob!!!) and I wanna start coding doors

Hello :)

> but, I don't want to use Amos, C, E, Or Hisoft Basic.. I'd like to use
> Blitz..

I would of at the time too, it`s much faster than AMOS. and probably
HSB.

> Now there is a limited doorpack available, which allows creations of very
> basic doors!! (It's attached) and it also needs a file to reside in C:
> which is not ideal..

It sucks.

> What I wanna do is create some functions that'll open the required
> Msgports, and allow me to do my doors..

Simple. As long as you know what you are piping down that msgport in
order to get a response. Does Max`s have a doc on creating Doors?
or perhaps a specification?

> Now I know that I need to interface with the "DOORCONTROL" msg port, and
> reply with the "DOORREPLY" port (I think).

Humm if those are the ports yeah probably.

> Firstly how do I get the msgport from Maxs (Do I need to get the task name
> of the program?). Then do I need to open the msg ports?

First of you need to do somthing like this:

MaxsPort.l=FindPort_("DOORCONTROL")

If MaxsPort.l=0
  End
Else... <Continue program>



MaxsPort.l then has the memory location of the port 
(was it you that asked for the msgports examples the other
week that david sent to the list? Those are probably the
best source of information on this.)

> Any advice, help would be greatly useful, coz I've loads of ideas for
> doors, and coupled with Blitz's power (Compared to Amos's) the doors could
> be stunning!!

<DownerTime>
Shame there arnt that many BBS people left to see them.
</DownerTime>

