For additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_98" "Re: BitMap Scrolling problem"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 14 Jul 1999 20:57:39 -0500
Subject: Re: BitMap Scrolling problem
X-UIDL: 7c5a5e2139c80bbbeb367531a7d74cc3

Hi Tony

On 14-Jul-99, Tony Rolfe wrote:
> Can anyone help please?

I'll try...
> 
> I'm doing the following sequence:
> 
> Use BitMap 1
> VWait
> Scroll .......
> BitMapToWindow 1,1,.....
> 
> 
> When the bitmap hits the window, there are frequently stray pixels, as
> though not all the bitmap scrolled properly.

Are you scrolling the text from another bitmap onto this one? 
Or is this a "superbitmap" (larger than the window) and you are scrolling
the text up or down from another area?

If it's the second, you could try skipping the scroll bit altogether, and
simply scroll it by using the sourceX and sourceY parameters of
"BitmapToWindow"
> 
> Hard to describe, but I have lines of text in the bitmap and I'm
> scrolling up or down, much like TED.   It is as though some of the
> pixels in some of the characters in some lines are staying where they
> were but the rest of the character has moved.
> 
> Any ideas?    Is this related to the getashape problem?

Maybe - the problem with GetAShape is that on faster processors it isn't
waiting for the blitter to finish.

I don't know if the Scroll command uses the blitter...

You could try adding a :
"WaitBlit_" before the "BitMapToWindow" command.

And move the "VWait" to just before the "BitMapToWindow" too.

It might help...

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



