@NODE "Mail_100" "Blitz Basics "MUIDoMethod""
From: Daniel Allsopp <daniel@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 14 Jul 1999 17:04:04 +0100
Subject: Blitz Basics "MUIDoMethod"
X-UIDL: 2437c89176f512d0b8488e66847b55e9

MUI'ers of the list,

I've been doing some tests with some external MCC's and have come across a
nasty limitation of Blitz Basics version of MUIDoMethod.

In Blitz syntax I want to do this (which is allowed in C) :

*text=AllocVec_(300*1024,$10000)
*buf=*text

    *buf=MUIDoMethod(#editor,#MUIM_TextEditor_ExportText)

    If openfile(1,"RAM:text.txt")
        Fileoutput 1
            Print Peek$(*buf)
        Closefile 1
    end if

FreeVec_(*text)

and the resulting file should be my text which is placed in the *buf by the
MUIDoMethod.

Only problem is, Blitzs version of MUIDoMethod can't be used as a function.
i.e. it can't be used to return anything.

Is there any other way of doing it?

-- 
Cheers,
    Daniel

