@NODE "Mail_105" "Re: Blitz Bitmap object structure"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 22 Jul 1999 07:19:49 -0500
Subject: Re: Blitz Bitmap object structure
X-UIDL: bb8948047a330ebccfaa844c080caa54

Hi Damir

On 22-Jul-99, Damir Arh wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> Where could I get information on Blitz Bitmap structure. It seems to me
> that it's not the same as the intuition window structure. I was using the
> amigalibsII.res and was trying todo the following:
> 
>  *MyWin._Window=Addr Window(1)

^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
This is the problem.  You are giving the address of the Blitz window Object
(structure) to the OS, not the actual address of the window.

Try this instead:

*MyWin._Window=Peek.l(Addr Window(1))

This will return a pointer to the actual OS window structure which is what
you need to use the OS commands.  

It is not the same as the Blitz Object (structure)

For info on the Blitz object structures, load in the BB2 objtypes.res file.

-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



