@NODE "Mail_108" "Re: Blitz CLI compiler."
Date: Mon, 12 Jul 1999 18:00:06 +1200
From: Julian Kinraid <jkinraid@clear.net.nz>
X-Accept-Language: en-GB,en
Subject: Re: Blitz CLI compiler.
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 9e66936d134a3269f18ff0426fd1dea0

Rob Hutchinson wrote:
> 
> Hello, and what not,
> 
>    I`m just wondering if anyone has tried that "BC" Blitz
> CLI compiler on Aminet by Christopher Jennings?
> 
> I dont know if Chris is on here, but I`ve gotta say it,
> it`s tottally pants!!... It uses ABSMouse and the like to open
> blitz and then move the mouse into the areas of the screen
> where things should be and ClickButton`s them. ahahahah.
> 
> But it got me thinking, I wonder if I CLI compiler could be
> written to open blitz iconified, and then create an executable
> and close it seamlessly?
> 
> I`m not good with ARexx though so I dont know, what
> y`all think?

'fraid not.  When Blitz is iconified, sending an arexx message to Blitz
won't work, and something will go wrong when Blitz is uniconified.  When
Blitz is iconified (actually, it's SuperTed's fault), it only expects to
recieve an uniconify message, not an arexx message.  And it can't handle
an arexx message if it is sent :(  If the 'Open Blitz' thing that Steven
Matty was talking about happens, it should be fairly easy to add that
functionality though.

--
Julian Kinraid ....... jkinraid@clear.net.nz ....... ICQ:17257217
"je suis american, please cook my steak again"

