@NODE "Mail_115" "Re: BlitzLibMan Vs DefLibMan"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 20 Jul 1999 06:56:45 -0500
Subject: Re: BlitzLibMan Vs DefLibMan
X-UIDL: bfa0746f7675eda8f25d8da563670444

Hi Rob

On 19-Jul-99, Rob Hutchinson wrote:
> Hello, and what not,
> 
>    Which y`all think is better? BlitzLibMan or DefLibMan.
> Personally I prefer the latter, cos the first crashes ;)
> (and DefLibMan looks more stylish :))

I mostly use DefLibMan (I think - that's the one with the resizable listview
window and the picture of the "Blitz" guy on it?) It's easy, quick, and
looks good.
And shows that you can make a nice resizable GUI without resorting to MUI or
other GUI libraries.

But BlitzLibMan has some useful features too, like showing a libraries
command list and the ability to change clashing lib numbers.

I'm surprised it crashes for you - I never had any problems with either one.

The only drawback is that you must put all your 3rd party libs into
Blitzlibs/userlibs/ since it won't recognize other directories like
"otherlibs/"

And no matter what it says, DO NOT EVER use library #1 for a library number.
 Libraries #0 and #1 are the actual compiler's libraries used for commands
like "Repeat", "If", "End", etc...

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



