Hi David

On 21-Jul-99, David McMinn wrote:

> In my previous quote, the important word is "was" :) I decided that I
> didn't have enough time to do something, so I never started it. However, I
> am still trying to find out how to get the token numbers.
> 
>> I also wanted to add an "fd.convert" routine to it, and a new library
>> "installer" with built-in clash checking.  
> 
> Hmmm. Must. Steal. NewFDConvert. Source.

Actually, it's included in the archive  ;)
> 
> What do you mean for library installer? A makedeflibs that checks for
> clashing token names / library numbers?

Well, sort of.  I was going to do it like the bit I added to
"New(er)FDConvert" - 

It would check the token names/lib numbers and offer the chance to correct
them, then simply "Execute_" the makedeflibs program (since there are at
least two versions I know of)...

And it would do the same checking when "FdConverting".

But, again, without a proper token-parsing routine, it's impossible.

BTW, my token parsing routine DOES work - the problem is that there is
something called "dumbtokens" in some libraries which are not tokenizing
commands, but they do use a token number.

They throw my parsing routines off by one token each time I run into one
since it doesn't recognize them. 

Later...
-- 

