Date: Fri, 23 Jul 1999 12:37:40 +0100
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Character case
X-UIDL: 1b7b1bf23963c0279ea59078ed9fd1d1

Hi again,

If I wanted to convert case of a character, including non-English characters 
(i.e. accented chars, Russian, Greek, etc), would it be as simple as this (for 
upper->lower case):

If (character is between 65 and 90) or (character is between 192 and 223)
    Bitwise OR 32 with character code
End If

I know the normal letters are between 65 and 90 and that accented are between 
192 and 223, as well as some other letters on this font map I'm looking at, but 
I don't know where letters from totally different languages are, like Russian, 
Greek, etc.

Using locale.library is not an option.

Any help would cure some annoyance.
Thanks.

-- 
