Organization: wanadoo.fr
Subject: Re: Character case
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 97581f36e6573f71108d8485dcfa4f85

David McMinn wrote:
> 
> Hi again,

Hi David,

> I know the normal letters are between 65 and 90 and that accented are between
> 192 and 223, as well as some other letters on this font map I'm looking at, but
> I don't know where letters from totally different languages are, like Russian,
> Greek, etc.

Ascii codes only offers 256 values and this number isn't enough to
describe languages except latin. The 16-bit Unicode system (used by
Java) is dedicated to all the character sets.

Maybe greeks, russian, japanese ... have their own Ascii table
(non-latin) ?

Cheers,

		Mathias

