@NODE "Mail_151" "Cool Idea #5378"
From: "Vic E Babes" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Cool Idea #5378
Date: Wed, 21 Jul 1999 19:18:21 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 1000bba07ab10318cb3782b608b9c0d4

I`ve just had another idea for the new OS.

Why do gadgets have to have their own variables?

Why can`t they just be set to point to your own variables - that way you
wouldn`t have to mess about with GTGetAttrs blah, as your own variables
would be automatically adjusted.

There might be a slight problem with the `type`, but nothing that couldn`t
be overcome.  They use pointers to everything else, so why not variables?

Time passes...

Mmmm.  Actually, it`s just occurred to me that you might want to know what
the new value is, before accepting it - though slider gadgets, etc should be
set to certain limits anyway - imagine a palette editor, where the slider
gadgets automatically change the palette.  And GTMX gadgets should be fine.

Oh well.

VIC



---------------------------------------------------------------------
