For additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_152" "Re: Cool Idea #5378"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 21 Jul 1999 17:53:43 -0500
Subject: Re: Cool Idea #5378
X-UIDL: 04c1cfdc2e68accbab8635cd5a0c8635

Hi Vic

On 21-Jul-99, Vic E Babes wrote:
> I`ve just had another idea for the new OS.
> 
> Why do gadgets have to have their own variables?
> 
> Why can`t they just be set to point to your own variables - that way you
> wouldn`t have to mess about with GTGetAttrs blah, as your own variables
> would be automatically adjusted.

Well, actually your program doesn't "own" the gadgets - Intuition does. 
That is why you must "ask" intuition for the attributes of the gadget, if
and when you want them.  The big advantage is that intuition takes care of
all the details for you (like drawing the "pressed" gadget when it is being
held down, centering the text in the button, drawing the "cycle" symbol for
you, etc...)  This is also what permits those nice hacks like MCP and
VisualPrefs to change the look of the gadgets for you.

The little bit of coding you have to do to get the information from
Intuition is nothing compared to what you'd have to do to create and
maintain a gadgetlist on your own  ;)

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



