@NODE "Mail_154" "Re: Cool Idea #5378"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 22 Jul 1999 20:11:37 -0500
Subject: Re: Cool Idea #5378
X-UIDL: ee111217d4907d002775848175d410a6

Hi Vic

On 22-Jul-99, Vic E Babes wrote:
>> Well, actually your program doesn't "own" the gadgets - Intuition does.
>> That is why you must "ask" intuition for the attributes of the gadget, if
>> and when you want them. 
>> 
> 
> Yeah, I know all that, I still don`t see what the problem is with having
> it `point` to a variable instead of having its own though.

Well, there probably is a way to go through the OS and get the pointers to
where Intuition keeps the gadget variables information if you want to go to
the trouble.
But what if someone changes a gadget while your program is in the middle of
a calculation with it's value?

And you'd also loose the ability to quque up the incoming events, and flush
the quque if you wanted to. 

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



