@NODE "Mail_165" "Re: copymem :("
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 25 Jul 1999 08:14:20 -0500
Subject: Re: copymem :(
X-UIDL: ac12753f24735a4b5fdc8251841093b1

--BOUNDARY.1748637584.2

Hi Oliver

On 25-Jul-99, Oliver Marks wrote:

>>>>> CopyMem_ cmem,cp\cp_Chunky,(320*200)
>>>>> the above line of code bring up a syntax error when copying to a
>>>>> newtype any ideas why. ?

BTW, you are NOT copying anything into the NewType here - rather, the memory
is being copied to the chunky buffer, which is somewhere else in memory. 
Only the pointer to this memory is in the NewType.

I would think the InitialChunky command (or whatever the name was) should be
allocating the memory for this buffer, then putting the pointer into the
NewType for you.

> I have tryed some of the ideas above but the code is still falling
> over when trying to copy to the newtype it works fine if it is a plain
> variable but causes a syntax error when using a newtype and i have no
> idea why?

Have you tried copying the cp_Chunky into a plain variable and using that
for the command?

Please save off the little attachment and look at it in a text reader - I
can't get YAM to include the "*" symbol sometimes...

If that works, great.  Just leave it that way.
If not, it has to be something wrong with the NewType.
> 
> If anyone wants to look at the code i can send it to you it not very
> big as all i am trying to do is display a bitmap on my bvision it is
> using chunky library and tythe code is an attempt at converting it
> from c so some of it could be wrong like the newtype.

You can send me a copy - I don't know if I can test it here, as I don't have
a GFX card or the library you are using, but maybe I can see something. 
Also send a copy of the "C" source.
> 
> Anyone know what -> does in c

It means the same as our "\" - it gives the location in the structure

so, in C:  x=cp -> cp_Chunky
in Blitz   x=cp\cp_Chunky

-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748637584.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="yam"
Content-Description: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>


*chunky=cp\*cp_Chunky
bytelen.l=320*200
CopyMem_ cmem,*chunky,bytelen


--BOUNDARY.1748637584.2

