@NODE "Mail_175" "Re: Default tool"
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Default tool
Date: Mon, 5 Jul 1999 15:39:22 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: c6ddf461f14899b28c46f4da274a8512

>Dave churned out *this* drivel:
>
>> No need, the problem is with amigalibs.res, Change the
>> '&*do\do_DefaultTool' to 'peek.l(*do+50)' and that should work.
>
>Well done...I've attached the finished version for anyone that wants it...
>
>How the hell do you find that kind of thing?!


Years of assembly programming the miggy ;). I think the main problem is that
Disk Object has an entry at offset 48 called do_type, which is normally
reported as

byte   name                             C                Modula-2
ML
48      do_Type                   UBYTE          STRPTR              UWORD
50      do_DefaultType

hmmm...so it`s either 1 a byte, 2 a long, or 3 a word depending what
language you use, and I assume the problem is that all the amigalibs.res
files come from the C includes, and not the assembly ones, which I believe
to be correct. (so even under C you`d have had that problem..so don`t feel
too bad!)

Dave



