> computer :(
> 
> Can someone else try this and see what it does?

John is right - you shouldn't need the &.  I fixed this part by doing a :

MaxLen dt$=255 

- now it will print out 255 characters of garbage without the "&" instead of
crashing.

Not much help - but I think the real problem is that the structure is wrong
- or Blitz is accessing it wrong, or something...  It doesn't work with
Fred's NCS Amigalibs.res or with the AmigalibsII.res either...

I also tried putting my own string into *do\do_DefaultTool before reading
it.
And yes, it works fine that way!

But doing a "PutDiskObject_" with the newly altered string winds up putting
only the first character into the icon's Default Tool field...

Again, not much help :(

The RIToolTypes library can set a new Default Tool without any problem, but
it doesn't have any way to read it.  Nothing in my copy of the NCSToolTypes
library for this either.

And there isn't any function in the AutoDocs ...

Later...
-- 


