Subject: Dim Question !!
X-UIDL: 3880649dd45058387c89633804324bcb

Hello, All Blitzers

I have encounter a problem with the Dim or Dim List function in a program, the
problem is:

NEWTYPE.item
aitem.w
bitem$
End NEWTYPE
 
Dim List test.item(100)

When i use a Dim later, for create a bigger List, example:
Dim List test.item(110)
The blitz don't free the memory of previous Dim List test.item(100), the blitz
add a new Dim List for Dim List test.item(110) without free the older (Dim
List test.item(100)) i have tried to use
ClearList test() before Dim List test.item(110), but it don't free the memory
of the List and it's a big problem when i make lot of Dim
because i lose lot of memory for nothing !!.

Anyone have a solution for free a Dim List in memory PLEASE ???

In the hope of a solution
Thanks all

BYE !!!!
