@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_182" "Re: Dim Question !!"
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Dim Question !!
Date: Sun, 4 Jul 1999 17:03:58 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 9721ed5e0a1aedce40f83e8a80a2f75a

Hi,

>> Anyone have a solution for free a Dim List in memory PLEASE ???
>>
>Use David Newton's DLL functions.   Then you don't have to dim the
>list.


Thanks for the plug ;)...the money`s in the post!

>Having to dim the size of a linked list is probably the most stupid
>thing Blitz has done (bet that starts a counter thread!).


It is and it isn`t, you have to remember that blitz was written for the 68k
(that`s why no 020+ asm opcodes can be directly compiled by it). The idea
was to have the fastest list possible, but just allocating the list to the
maximum once. What happens is blitz stores the linked list in a single block
of memory, but keeps track of the used items in a list, and keeps track of
the free items in a list and this saves you having to allocmem/freemem
(which is slow on an a500) all the time, and only requires a couple of
instructions to add or delete a item (ie, just change the links in the
list), but gives you that preset list size problem (good for games, bad for
databases).

Dave



