RE:      EdHT *Ed*itor for *H*yper*T*ext - DEVELOPMENT:
Greetings! Blitzers,

I subscribed a week or two ago and have been lurking/listening intently.
Although I am not a Blitz programmer I was involved heavily with the 
development of EdHT and Andrew Guthrie was amazingly able to implement
nearly all of the changes I suggested.

     A prolonged illness of the author of EdHT (Andrew Guthrie) came 
     to an end in 1998 when Andrew sadly passed away. I know from 
     EdHT's credits that many of you knew Andrew from this list. 

     Throughout 1997 I was priveleged to get to know Andrew as sole 
     beta tester for EdHT and received about 20 as yet UnReleased 
     versions of EdHT. 

     The SOURCE code (Blitz Basic for the Amiga) has been left to me 
     and I am hoping that development will continue via ANY interested
     Blitz coders, perhaps as a (Linux style:) public development.
     This could happen via my web site where I could set up a USER
     PASS system for any blitz coders prepared to iron out a few
     bugs in the latest EdHT 0.5 Alpha 17.6 as I'd like to 

    If I am not mistaken PARTs of Blitz source are compiled into a
    binary, so it may or may not? be feasible for different coders
    to work on different PARTs of the source? 

     Any questions about EdHT can be directed to me...
     Andrew Barker - boab@agn.net.au
     or boab@laa.com.au - Please put "EdHT Blitz" as SUBJECT.

Best Regards, Andrew
