--BOUNDARY.1748298360.1
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hi Mikkel

On 25-Jul-99, Mikkel L=F8kke wrote:
> Hello.
> =

> I have a question that's NOT about EGGS, CHICKENS, or other FOWL langua=
ge.
> (So it might even have a little relevance to this list).
> =

> I'm trying to deternime the CLI path my program was run from, to no ava=
il,
> by reading through the autodocs I found the rather usefull command,
> unfortunately I seem to be a little too stuppid to get it working.
> =

> Does anyone know how to get it working ? Or if there is another way to =
get
> the "Expanded" (that's full path, starting with the device name) of the=

> current directory ?

Here's a little function, from James Boyd's "Stats/Functs" file that retu=
rns
the current directory (full path) of the cli it is run from (the CD of th=
e
CLI itself, I mean, not the path to the command).  I hope this is what yo=
u
want?

Or, if you mean you want the full path to the program itself, I have
attached another one for that.  It's also from the same file.

I recommend that anybody who is interested in OS routines get a copy of t=
his
file (it is in Aminet/dev/basic/)  It has lots of useful system routines,=

and also is a good way to learn how to create such routines yourself. =


Later...
-- =

Facts do not cease to exist because they are ignored.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748298360.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="Currdir.asc"

;-----------------------------------------------------------------

; Function : CurrentDir {}

; Author : James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk

; Returns a string with the current directory name
; only works with CLI-run programs :(

Function.s CurrentDir{}

*stringbuffer = AllocMem_(255, 0)
suc.l=GetCurrentDirName_(*stringbuffer,255)

If suc
  cdirname$=Peek$(*stringbuffer)
  Function Return cdirname$
  Else Request "Info","Couldn't get current directory name!","Oh..."
EndIf

End Function

; demo :

; a$=CurrentDir{}

; Print a$
; MouseWait:End

;-----------------------------------------------------------------

--BOUNDARY.1748298360.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="ProgsPath.asc"

;-----------------------------------------------------------------

; Author : Nick Clover - nick@bauk.freeserve.co.uk
; Returns a string with the program's full path
; must be compiled into an exec to work!
; otherwise the path will be "SYS:" if run from the
; Blitz editor...

Function.s ProgsDir{}

  MaxLen path$=200
  NameFromLock_ GetProgramDir_(),&path$,200
  path$=Peek$(&path$)
  If Right$(path$,1)<>":" AND Right$(path$,1)<>"/"
    path$+"/"
  EndIf
  ;If path$="SYS:" Then path$="I only work when compiled!"
Function Return path$
End Function

;---------------------------------------------------------


--BOUNDARY.1748298360.1

