Hi Leigh

On 21-Jul-99, Leigh Parry wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> Can somebody with a graphics card (or not), answer the following.
> 
> I am opening an 800*600 screen and would like the best ID for it (
> probably dblpal).I have a screen which will open up either normal
> Hires-Lace or this 800*600 mode - but what would it's viewmode i.d. be?
> 
> can anybody help?

Well, sort of.  I can point you in the right direction, but I have no idea
how to make it work.  What you want is to use the OS function BestModeIDA_ 
which is explained in the graphics.library section of the autodocs.
> 
> Would the ID be the same for different GFX cards?

No.  In fact, as I understand it, it might not even be the same for the same
GFX card installed on a different system...

Personally, I'd recommend using a ScreenMode requester the first time the
program is run, limited to the sizes and resolutions you want.  Then you
could save the results to a tooltype or a prefs file or something for use
on future runs of the program.

I do have code for this, if you are interested.

Later...
