Mikkel wrote,
>What ? You only have 10 fingers ? :o>

Just thought I`d add a vaguely related comment on this topic.

Numerology is that nonsense that is supposed to tell you lots of stuff about
who you are and so forth.  The way that Numerologists arrive at their magic
numbers: the digits 0 to 9, is by adding numbers to gether, so

    25 = 2 + 5 = 7

The trouble with this is that numerology requires us to accept that it is a
universal principal that we count in decimal - as the same number written in
other bases would yield a different magic number!

Larry Niven and Jerry Pournelle wrote a book called "The Mote In God`s Eye"
in which there was an alien race that counted in OCTAL, because they only
had 8 fingers.

I think that this shows that numerology must be absolute nonsense.  In the
same way that Douglas Adams pointed out that Astrologists didn`t realize
that there was another planet near Pluto.

VIC



