@NODE "Mail_256" "Re: Interlace"
From: Rob Hutchinson <loki@sds.in2home.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 19 Jul 1999 07:54:33 +0100
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: Re: Interlace
X-UIDL: 1d9c5c7fce93f3f01ea2111c12ab1d6a

--BOUNDARY.274136816.1
Encoding: binary

Hello Donovan
     Hiya, Donovan... ,on 18-Jul-99 you mailed me about: Interlace! So I`ma reply`in...

[=> Hi all,
[=> 
[=>  Does anyone know a way to use interlaced screens in Blitz mode
[=> with the display library.  I can't seem to find any mention of
[=> using interlace in Blitz mode in the manual.

Sure do :).. Attached is the project that me and David McMinn were
working on to open a 256 Colour laced coplist. It took some doing to
get it to work in 256 colours, so making it use anything less could
be a pain. Also, remember that it will not work with most custom coplist
effects now, IE, DisplayScroll.

NB. Simon Hitchens Scan doubler REALLY didn`t like it very much at all,
    and it didn`t come out as interlaced on his mig. Though it did on
    everyone elses ;).. We never figured out why.

[=> 
-- 

Rob,
-- 
MAILTO:loki@sds.in2home.co.uk | #ICQ:# 27181384
#FAX:# 0870 0888470
#SDS FOUNDER:# URL: http://www.satanicdreams.freeserve.co.uk/
#PROJECT INFO:# Minimum Safe Distance [####------ 40% ish complete. ]
#HOME OF:# /MorrisTheMaggot, BB2MUIUpdate, TimeSwipe, NIB,/
/CTTM2, BlitzBFB, Prefs2000 & TMS. And too much other stuff./
[ Gene Rodenberry, 1921-1991  Shakka, when the walls fell. ]

--BOUNDARY.274136816.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="LacedCopList.ASC"

;
; Originally written by some guy ;)
; Updated to 256 cols by David McMinn.
; Align Fixed by Rob Hutchinson.
;
; DATED: 23/05/1999
;
; DESC: Opens a 256 colour Hi-Res LACED coplist and maintains it.
;
; EMail Updates to: dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk  OR
;                   loki@sds.in2home.co.uk
;

WBStartup
NoCli

#BPLMOD1=$108
#BPLMOD2=$10A
#BPLCON0=$100

#BITMAPSIZE=640
#MODULO=76

COP$=Mki$(#BPLMOD1)+Mki$(#MODULO)
COP$+Mki$(#BPLMOD2)+Mki$(#MODULO)
COP$+Mki$(#BPLCON0)+Mki$($8014)   ; was $f004

BitMap 0,#BITMAPSIZE,512,8
InitPalette 0,256

  ;--- Set this to a 640x512x8 picture on disk.
  ;
  LoadBitMap 0,"",0

InitCopList 0,44,256,$11518,8,256,-3   ; for 256 colour AGA
DisplayUser 0,0,COP$


Delay_ 50
BLITZ
CreateDisplay 0
DisplayBitMap 0,0
DisplayPalette 0,0
Use BitMap 0

SetInt 5
  If Peek($dff004)<0
    DisplayBitMap 0,0,0,0
  Else
    DisplayBitMap 0,0,0,1
  EndIf
End SetInt

MouseWait
End




--BOUNDARY.274136816.1

