@NODE "Mail_264" "Re: K`POO Blitting."
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: K`POO Blitting.
Date: Sun, 4 Jul 1999 01:24:26 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 931236f491dcd24abeab885b6231f596

Hi Rob,

>Hello, and what not,
>
>  Just wondering what those CPU blitting routines Dave (I think it
>was Dave?) are called, if they support buffered blits and
>where I can get them from? I`m sure I checked on aminet for them
>a while back and couldn`t find them!


Yep..guilty as charged! The problem is they were part of a set of routines
for all graphics for fastmem (fonts, shapes, bitmaps, drawing) in planar and
chunky, but I`ve never had enough time to spend on them, and only half
finished the fonts and drawing, and the blit routines weren`t comprehensive
(unlike mildred) because I`ve a lot of work on at the moment (pc and amiga).
Buffered blits would be quite easy but I`ve got no time to be adding and
updating the includes (and mildred is very good, even if you have to c2p for
aga).


Sorry I haven`t really helped,

Dave

P.s. I`m PRETTY sure it isn`t on aminet, but it should be in one of the
blitz-mailing list archives on aminet (I`d send you my copy, but the only
one I have is dodgy...I split my includes up and made it very buggy
unfortunately and it`s hard to track down bugs when your debugger can`t step
into included source files!!)




