@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_266" "Re: LEShapes library recovery"
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@free4all.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 21 Jul 1999 20:45:31 +0000
Subject: Re: LEShapes library recovery
X-UIDL: e0ab4aaf24e56a144307296a2c8adce0

Hello Ian

On 21-Jul-99, Ian Andrews wrote:

> Okay. I used to have the LEShapes library. Then I used compiled it along 
> with all my other libraries into a big deflibs file and deleted the 
> original .obj files. Now I need to compile a new deflibs file because I 
> need to add some new libraries. But I don't know where to find a copy of 
> the LEShapes library.
> 
> Is there any way I can get the LEShapes library back out of the deflibs 
> file I have so that I can recompile it along with everything else into a 
> new deflibs file.


Check out the blitz section of my web pages (address at bottom), you'll find
a prog which splits the 'acidlibs' into its seperate libraries just change
the file its opening to deflibs and it works (I've tried it and it worked).
You then have a large number of unknown libs (could be rectified, but as
these are third party libs then they could be any library)

Search through them until you find the lib you want and rename it.

I'd advise having a backup of acidlibs,deflibs and your blitzlibs: drawer
beforehand.

If you have any further probs, please contact me and i'll try to help.

-- 
