@NODE "Mail_268" "Libraries - hacked to death"
From: David McMinn <dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 23 Jul 1999 01:26:09 +0000
Organization: International House Of Mojo
Subject: Libraries - hacked to death
X-UIDL: c1c6a22199c19f01adf4f2b31f340b86

--BOUNDARY.2015896512.1
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hi-diddly-ho neighbours,

I've attached the results of my attempt to glean information from librari=
es. It
seems to work, but it only shows libnums, token nums and token strings an=
d help
strings for the token. It only works on external library files (i.e. .lib=
raryx
and .obj files, not acidllibs or deflibs). In the archive you'll find the=

source to the program, a source file with random tokens in it and an
explanation of a library file.

Actually the source of random tokens was just for checking Curt's Investi=
gator
program, which I think needs changing. The line which works out the libra=
ry
number should have +(cmd>127) instead of -(cmd>127).

Use it any way you want, hopefully someone will do this new library manag=
er
program that I've been going on about.

-- =

