@NODE "Mail_272" "Re: Libs help"
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 20 Jul 1999 03:26:10 +0100
Subject: Re: Libs help
X-UIDL: 11cdf4c8854b8c445e21f59dd06179ce

Neil Bullock churned out *this* drivel:

> Ok, I'm not someone who knows the inner workings of Blitz as some people
> on here seem to, I only know how to program using some of the commands
> that come with Blitz. However, why is it that I cannot use the Big Deflibs
> from the extras disk when I've installed any lib from aminet? What am I
> doing wrong?

If you're getting commands from the Deflib not tokenising or tokenising
with the wrong name, you've probably got a number conflict - get BlitzLibMan
from dev/basic, and go to the Check For Conflicting Libnums menu item...

Then you can change the conflicting libraries' numbers by clicking
on the Change libnum (or similar) button followed by a double-click
on the library in the list...

BlitzLibMan will suggest a free libnum, but starts from 1 and goes up,
whereas it should start from 255 and work backwards...get the similarly
named LibMan from dev/basic which'll display all the used/conflicting
numbers (but won't let you change 'em!). Try and use the highest free
numbers available...

Hope this helps...

See ya,
-- 
