@NODE "Mail_275" "Re: Libs help"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 19 Jul 1999 18:44:50 -0500
Subject: Re: Libs help
X-UIDL: 12219e40925de28f289cacc62d8dcb20

Hi Neil

On 19-Jul-99, Neil Bullock wrote:

>>> Hope this helps...
>> It does indeed. Thanks very much :)
> 
> Well, it seemed to. All libs I install now work in perect harmony :) but I
> still don't get any of the commands I get from installing BigDeflibs from
> the Blitz extras disk. Is there a specific library I need to install and
> where is it?

There should be a directory inside your Blitzlibs/ directory called
"Otherlibs/" or possibly "Userlibs/"

In one of these, there should be a load of libraries, such as
"ElmoreDosLib.obj", "NeilsReqtoolsLibrary.obj", etc...

If you don't find these, check the disks or CD and find them.  If you have
the disk version of Blitz, they may be .lha'd somewhere.  Possibly in
"libs.dev.lha"  Just keep seaching until you find them - they are somewhere
in the distribution.

Anyway, copy all the files that end in ".obj" into Blitzlibs/otherlibs/
along with any new libraries you want to add.  And nothing else!  If there
are any docs or examples with them, copy them to a different place, not
inside a Blitzlibs/ subdirectories 

Then run the "MakeDefLibs" command, or preferrably use the LibMan program if
you have it to create a new Deflibs file.

When you run "MakeDefLibs" it scans through all your Blitzlibs/ directories
and puts all the libraries into DefLibs - so, they must all be put
somewhere inside Blitzlibs/ first.  

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



