@NODE "Mail_290" "Re: Menus"
From: "Vic E Babes" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Menus
Date: Sun, 4 Jul 1999 12:41:28 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 1699c7a0e9ebcc88278f25692549f4ab

Daniel
> Exactly how does the command MenusOff work?
>
> Am I correct in thinking that you send either the MenusOff or the Menus
Off
> command straight after you've opened the window you want no menus on?
>
> I've done this but I've still got menus when clicking the RMB.....is there
> an OS command that does a similar thing?

Yeah, I`ve used this several times for Intution based map-editors, where I
use the RMB for deleting and the LMB for printing.  Yes, you should use
MENUS OFF straight after creating the window, and you will need to ADDIDCMP
(whatever the value is for CatchRMBEvents - can`t remember what it is
off-hand - but FLAGS will tell you if you`re running that.

Also - make sure that the relevant window is activated.

If you still have problems let me know, and I`ll check the code in one of my
programs.

VIC



