@NODE "Mail_306" "MSD Requires Game Programmer."
From: Rob Hutchinson <loki@sds.in2home.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 20 Jul 1999 22:24:36 +0100
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: MSD Requires Game Programmer.
X-UIDL: 7a7807dc113444a6a8a9e45ec8474020

Hello, and what not,

    As most of you may be aware, we have been writing a game
called MSD for some time now, unfoutunatly one of the programmers
has had to drop out (possibly for the duration
of the development period) which is a shame but beyond his control.

Anyway, the game is already half-developed, I know there are a lot 
of GREAT programmers on this list. And I wonder if there is anyone 
with good enough BLITZ-MODE/GameCreation skills to work on a
commercial game and jump into someone else`s work? Obviously
it will require a reasonably high level of mathematics.

This will also REQUIRE you to be able to keep in contact with
the other developers' (artists, musicians, etc) DAILY, Not weekly
or every other day. And be willing to drop all other projects to
work soley on /Minimum Safe Distance/. Also you must be able to give
the game a reasonable amount of attention daily.

Please reply to this EMail privatly if interested.

-- 

MSD Director, Rob,
-- 
MAILTO:loki@sds.in2home.co.uk | #ICQ:# 27181384
#FAX:# 0870 0888470
