@NODE "Mail_315" "Multi-Column reports"
From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 9 Jul 99 10:49:36 +1000
Subject: Multi-Column reports
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 75b7e9d7c20f51426efac3b9d75d1691

Some time ago someone mentioned needing the ability to produce
font-sensitive multi-column scrollable reports.

I've just about finished some routines which do just that (except they
use a scroller rather than a listview).    Each line of the report has
its own column structure (allows for multi-section reports) and each
column can have its own alignment (left, right, centred, decimal) and
its own colour).    It wouldn't be too difficult to add JAM mode and
font to each column if you really wanted.

They use a slightly modified version of David Newton's DLL routines
(all user functions are converted to statements - except for those
which really NEED to return a value - and errors are handled inside
the actual routine) but that wouldn't be a big change to undo.

It'll take a few days to hack them out of the mainline and wrap a
demo program round them - I'm tied up for the next week or so - but if
anyone is interested, I'll post them here or mail direct.

-- 
Tony Rolfe
Amiga 2000, 68030/25, 1+4Mb
www.shoalhaven.net.au/edgewater

