get a better idea.
 
>> Oh, and Anton, once again, this is not an attack on you or your
>> oppinion, I'm just sick and tired of people whinning who AMiGA are
>> "abandoning the AMiGA Classic". Well of course they are ! It's
>> ancient ! 32-bit motherboard, 16Megs of RAM, 2 megs of chip. If it
>> wheren't so damned tragic, it would be a bloody joke. I for one would
>> rather have the AMiGA BACK on the shelves, than lets P5 turn it into
>> an ATARI. (Oh yes, they're still arround, they have multiple 060's
>> and PPC's (And they run Linux too BTW :o> Ec ept they use the whole
>> bloody thing, not just the kernel) and you're never gonna GUESS the
>> price tag)...

  The Amiga Classic can go get Fucked as far as I'm concerned :) 
I'm sick of the 040 on running slow on CPU intensive tasks. My IDE drive
is capable of 33M a sec max throughput, and on the 1200 it runs at
about 1.2M a sec- HAH!  
 
>> Sorry again Anton... I'm getting abit carried away, I'll just shut up
>> now, before I start off again.

  That's ok :) It's interesting to hear other developers views, as what
we chose will have a massive effect on these machines- and the last
thing we want is to split the Amiga community! Also, it's rather hard
to get the true picture at the moment, so any comments are welcome!

>  I am sure Anton realises that you weren't attacking him.

>  I don't blame Anton for getting excited about this developement. It
> is very significant, though it may mean trouble. The plans of Amiga
> will actually make it easier for other companys to start new platforms
