@NODE "Mail_337" "Re: Newtypes :("
From: Damir Arh <damir.arh@guest.arnes.si>
Date: Fri, 23 Jul 1999 09:26:59 +0100
Subject: Re: Newtypes :(
X-UIDL: 8ac8e970bb6dfaed9317db30a1f14450

Hello everyone

On 22-Jul-99, Oliver Marks shared his opinion:

> I have been trying to use a library with blitz i converted the fd file
> and got all the commands working i can not how ever figure out how to
> convert the c structures into blitz newtypes can some one please help?

I'll try to, though I could be wrong.

> the code is below and could you tell me what unsigned is and what long
> char and int and short are changed to i think i can figure out some of
> them but i am unsure about others like short?

Below is the struct, converted to Blitz.

NEWTYPE.ChunkyPort
  cp_Identifier.l         ; == CHKP ###
  *cp_Chunky.b            ; Memory allocated for the chunky data
  cp_cx.w                 ; Draw pen x position in buffer
  cp_cy.w                 ; Y pen
  cp_APen.b               ; Foreground pen
  cp_OPen.b               ; Outline pen
  cp_BPen.b               ; Background pen
  cp_IPen.b               ; Shine/shadow pen
  cp_Flags.w              ; Flags which are the same as graphics/rastport.h
  *cp_Font.TextFont       ; Font to use for text rendering
  *cp_TxtChunky.b         ; Chunky data buffer used for text rendering ###
  cp_TxHeight.w           ; Height of the text ###
  cp_TxBaseline.w         ; Baseline of the text ###
  cp_TxStyle.w            ; Softstyles in graphics/text.h plus these...
  cp_NoFree.w             ; TRUE if buffer was grabbed from a memory
location ###
  cp_BufSize.l            ; Number of bytes used for cp_Chunky
  cp_Width.w              ; Pixel width of buffer
  cp_Height.w             ; Pixel height of buffer
  *cp_Colours.ColoursCP   ; Pointer to colour palete data or NULL if none
###
  *cp_ScrollCP.ChunkyPort ; @{bg shine}(V4)@{bg background} Used by
CHK_Scroll() ###
  cp_Reserved1.l          ; ###
  cp_Reserved2.l          ; ###
  cp_Reserved3.l          ; ###
  cp_Reserved4.l          ; ###
  cp_Reserved5.l          ; ###
  cp_Reserved6.l          ; ###
  cp_Reserved7.l          ; ###
End NEWTYPE

> Any help will be appreciated :)

Hope this helps.


Kind regards from Slovenia
-- 
