Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="ObtainBestPen.asc"
Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Description: Use of ObtainBestPenA_()


; Function : RGBPen { r, g, b, precision }

; Author : James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
; Adapted from Simon Hitchen's (simon@gadge.u-net.com) code

; Returns the number of the screen pen you should use for
; whatever colour you want. You supply the RGB values.

; NOTE that you MUST have a screen currently in use!

; Returns a value of -1 if there are no shareable colours
; available in the screen. Although I've been naughty in the
; demo, you should really check the returned value. I've just
; tested what happens when you supply WColour with a value of
; -1, and it doesn't cause any problems, but the colour is
; unpredictable, so it's up to you whether you check it or not!
; Also, remember that other commands may not be happy with -1
; and may cause crashes!

; Valid values for "precision" parameter :

; #PRECISION_EXACT (-1) ; Read the autodocs for what these
; #PRECISION_IMAGE (0)  ; values do. You probably won't
; #PRECISION_ICON  (16) ; see much difference whatever
; #PRECISION_GUI   (32) ; you use!

Function.l RGBPen { r.l, g.l, b.l, precision.b }

  r LSL 24 ;
  g LSL 24 ; adjust to "32-bit left justified long value"
  b LSL 24 ;

  *scrn.Screen=3DPeek.l(Addr Screen(Used Screen))
  *view.ViewPort=3D*scrn\_ViewPort ; *** Remove underscore from "_ViewPor=
t" if you get "Offset not found" error!
  *cmap.ColorMap=3D*view\ColorMap

  pen.l=3DObtainBestPenA_(*cmap,r,g,b,precision)

  Function Return pen
End Function

; demo :

 FindScreen 0
 Window 0,20,20,400,150,$140e,"",1,2

 NPrint ""
 WColour RGBPen {255,0,0,#PRECISION_GUI}
 NPrint "I'm in red!"

 WColour RGBPen {0,255,0,#PRECISION_GUI}
 NPrint "I'm in green!"

 WColour RGBPen {255,255,0,#PRECISION_GUI}
 NPrint "I'm in yellow!"

 WColour RGBPen {0,0,255,#PRECISION_GUI}
 NPrint "I'm in blue!"

 NPrint ""
 WColour 2; RGBPen {0,0,0,#PRECISION_GUI}
 NPrint "I want black, which RGBPen {0,0,0,#PRECISION_GUI}"
 Print "tells me is pen number ":
 black.l=3DRGBPen {0,0,0,#PRECISION_GUI}
 WColour black:Print black
 MouseWait:End


--BOUNDARY.1749315176.2

