@NODE "Mail_344" "Off-topic, but on-topic as well? DRIVE SPECS"
From: Gaz-JD/FX-s^D <gaz@jokerd.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 30 Jul 1999 16:02:21 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: Off-topic, but on-topic as well? DRIVE SPECS
X-UIDL: 0a7648eb66052af80c3115cfc41a8cbc

--BOUNDARY.31141192.1

Hi,
   You know when you put a pc disk into a floppy drive and you get
DF0:NDOS or DF0:BAD, and when u put a CDDA disk in under AmiCDFS 2 you
get CD0:CDDA? Well how can you detect the presence of this. Here's the
reason:

I want to make a script/program which runs at bootup, detects if a
CDDA disk is present, by looking for CD0:CDDA and then launching a CD
Player. 

Either in Blitz2 or standard AmigaDOS script. 

Check out the pic I took at the WoA of the NG. Jay Miner comes back to
haunt us? And look at the purple eyes on the fire extinguisher in the
middle left of the picture :)))

I'll prolly get flamed to buggery for sending this mail to the list,
but what the hell.
Cya!
Gaz.
