@NODE "Mail_346" "OS 3.5 [off topic]"
From: "Vic E Babes" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: OS 3.5 [off topic]
Date: Sat, 3 Jul 1999 13:53:48 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 36ae0093e266c969ee7a6653417f3065

I`ve just been reading the latest updates on OS 3.5, and it states that
they`ve added a progress indicator for DELETE/COPY - I hope this doesn`t
mean we`re going to get stupid animations of pieces of paper flying out of
folders like Windows - when I delete something, I want it deleting - I don`t
want to wait for it to display a *!@^* animation of it!!!!!!  They`re just
to give dimwitted PC users a graphical representation of what the computer
is doing.

I might do a 24-bit full screen, ray-traced animation of a dustbin lorry
backing into a yard, with a man getting out and emptying a dustbin, before
driving off again, and send it to Microsoft to see if they want to add it to
Windows 2000.

VIC



