@NODE "Mail_349" "Re: OS 3.5 [off topic]"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 04 Jul 1999 07:12:20 -0500
Subject: Re: OS 3.5 [off topic]
X-UIDL: e7d833d2faf2f3e06ce2f25326d68c11

Hi Andrew

On 03-Jul-99, Andrew Guard wrote:
> Well, well Vic E Babes, OK then but...
>> I`ve just been reading the latest updates on OS 3.5, and it states that
>> they`ve added a progress indicator for DELETE/COPY - I hope this doesn`t
>> mean we`re going to get stupid animations of pieces of paper flying out
>> of folders like Windows - when I delete something, I want it deleting - I
>> don`t want to wait for it to display a *!@^* animation of it!!!!!!
>> They`re just to give dimwitted PC users a graphical representation of
>> what the computer is doing.

I'm not a dim-witted PC user (well, not a PC user, anyway..) but I like to
have a graphical representation of what the system is doing.

I agree about the animation, but a progress bar would be good.  What's the
point of a GUI if things aren't represented graphically?

> But why ow why, on windoze logo is falling a part on the side!  Has
> Micro$lop been try to say something for all this time. Think about it!

Yes, it's their version of a progress bar - everything seems fine at the
start, but the longer you use it, the more things go to pieces  ;)

Later...
