@NODE "Mail_354" "Performance issues"
From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 28 Jul 99 14:48:24 +1000
Subject: Performance issues
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 2cf19e62549a96e2469cd263a3da9253

In terms of execution speed, is there any difference between

Newtype .Thing
a.l
b.l
c.l
end newtype

deftype .Thing MyThing

1.  MyThing\a = 0,0,0

and 2.   MyThing\a=o
            MyThing\b=0
            MyThing\c=0

Or how about
If a = b then c = d
versus
if a = b
   c = d
endif

or is there any advantage to
a=b:c=d:e=f
against
a=b
c=d
e=f


and finally is there any advantage to doing a UsePath rather than
spelling it out in full?

Thanks

-- 
Tony Rolfe
Amiga 2000, 68030/25, 1+4Mb
www.shoalhaven.net.au/edgewater

