@NODE "Mail_356" "Re: Performance issues"
From: Sandy Brownlee <sandy@brownlee99.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 28 Jul 1999 21:09:45 +0100
Subject: Re: Performance issues
X-UIDL: e4f7b482bd415aad7458a31961767def

Hello David

On 28-Jul-99, you wrote:

 
> 
>> In terms of execution speed, is there any difference between
> 
> Ah, looks like its come to the desparate stage of trying to make program
> logic quicker ;)

Not that old trick again :-)
 
>> Or how about
>> If a = b then c = d
>> versus
>> if a = b
>>    c = d
>> endif
> 
> I'd heard someone say before that the second version is quicker, but I'm
> sure it would compile to the same code.

I seem to recall someone saying that with If...Then, the whole of the If
line must be read before execution of the next line.

So if there is a lot of stuff after the Then, put it into an If...End If,
because when the If condition ain't true, the conditional code won't be
unnecessarily read.

If you can understand that little sentence, you're a better man than I!

Regards,

        Sandy Brownlee

----------------------------------------

Now, Mr. Gates, it's an easy question: Chicken/Egg. Take your time.


