@NODE "Mail_359" "Re: Performance issues"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Thu, 29 Jul 1999 11:28:15 +0100
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Re: Performance issues
X-UIDL: bd51d0a2d479f1db013d9875a79adc39

Hi Tony

> I rather think that th eusepath version may be quicker since it could
> load the base address once rather than for each line of code. Still,
> nothing really significant either way.

It doesn't work like that though. The compiler changes
USEPATH blah
\aaa = 3

into blah\aaa = 3

Its all done at compile time, and is equivalent to typing blah\aaa = 3 into 
your source code. Its just there to make long lines fit into the 128 characters 
you've got to play with.


