@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_365" "Re: Plotting"
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Wed, 28 Jul 1999 13:49:46 +1200
Subject: Re: Plotting
X-UIDL: 5e26675dc2a139d523b46a2701ec1488

On 26-Jul-99, Sasu Lintula wrote:
 
> Yes yes, you sent a source to open an interleaved screen. That's not
> what I was looking after (althoug nice piece of code). I wanted to
> know if there's someone who could write a special optimized blitter
> line drawing routine for il-screen. This is causing me sleepless
> nights 'cause I think that kind of routine has a potential so please
> let me explain: As far as I know if you are using a some kind of c2p
> routine and want to draw even only one pixel on screen you have to do
> that using chunky-buffer (byte->buffer->|c2p|->bitplanes). Now with
> blitter you just have to set up blitter with proper texture and blit a
> vertical line. I don't get it why this shouldn't be faster than all
> kind of c2p conversions. Ok, c2p is handy if you have to update a
> whole screen at the same time but are you really doing that? And the
> side effect: if you are blitting (plotting) an object sized f.ex.
> 32x32 bytes and want to triple its size, just set blitters line height
> to 24 (on a 8-bpl screen) and you can draw a scaled object using as
> much vertical blits as drawing the smaller one. The routine could also
> be optimized to draw all bytes that have same value and are connected
> to each other at the same blit which is quite uselful for scalers. At
> least in theory it should be fast.

> Ok, now you all god-coders have had a good laugh. Wipe your tears and
> explain to me why this ain't a good idea and none won't use it ever:|

  Ok :)  Well it depends how much GFX work you want do do. If you have
lots of things on your screen, and doing transparency work (this is
very important for modern games), then you have to have a chunky buffer
and C2P. There's a limit what you can do with the Blitter- to do more
you have to use the CPU for blitting (assuming you've got an 030+.)
 
-- 
        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
      A500,DF1:,0.5MC,8.5MF,60HDD,WB3.1 &1.3/2.0 
    A1200,2M,CD-Rom,25/040,200/PPC ,WB3.0 
          
