@NODE "Mail_373" "Re: PowerBasic - Debug Files"
From: Rob Hutchinson <loki@sds.in2home.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 22 Jul 1999 17:53:47 +0100
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: Re: PowerBasic - Debug Files
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: fb6fc4ec746c8f21319680f493323c63

Hello Frederic
     Hiya, Frederic... ,on 22-Jul-99 you mailed me about: PowerBasic - Debug Files! So I`ma reply`in...

> 
>    Hello Blitzers,
> 
>    Here are the current powerbasic library test files, so if everyone
> on the list could test them and report all the bugs founds, it will be
> very great. All the examples are assumed you need at least Rom 3.0. Older
> OS versions is no more supported. Go on. This is the only restriction,
> all should tun fine on any Amiga. Say me if something goes wrong.

Nope all fine here.

Only, you are going more towards C with PowerBasic I see from the 
sources? This isn`t a bad thing but may put newbie programmers
off using it, and probably wont be very `BASIC'?

>    Testing have been done on:
> 
>    A1230/50 - 16 Mb Fast + Enforcer. No hits are reported.
> 
>    I've included the sources files, so you can see how all that is
> coded :-)

It looks very easy. I spoze this is the only way to get small
fast executables, but it is going to make it harder to use than
Blitz. Thing I like about Blitz most is the user has the choice
of exaclty HOW they want to code, using internal Window library
which is slower and creates bigger exe`s. Or do it completely with
the OS which would produce damn small EXE. Or even inbetween
and use the NLibs. (PB seems like the nlibs, a sort of inbetween.)

BTW, are there MUI,Direct-AGA-Hardware,Chunky,Shapes
libs? I think Blitz needs/needed a lot better shapes commands.

>        Good bye,
> 
-- 

Rob,
