X-UIDL: 13163a71820e709d0fee1709107c572d

Hello Anton
     Hiya, Anton... ,on 23-Jul-99 you mailed me about: Re: PowerBasic - Debug Files! So I`ma reply`in...

> On 23-Jul-99, Rob Hutchinson wrote:
> 
>> Only, you are going more towards C with PowerBasic I see from the 
>> sources? This isn`t a bad thing but may put newbie programmers
>> off using it, and probably wont be very `BASIC'?
> 
>   Only very slightly. Just a couple of pointers for Taglists etc. I
> think it's actually good as it helps you understand the OS better, and
> what's actually happening :)

I agree, it`s just moving away from the principals of BASIC code though
I thought. Oh well. WE will have to see.

>>>    Testing have been done on:
>>> 
>>>    A1230/50 - 16 Mb Fast + Enforcer. No hits are reported.
>>> 
>>>    I've included the sources files, so you can see how all that is
>>> coded :-)
> 
>> It looks very easy. I spoze this is the only way to get small
>> fast executables, but it is going to make it harder to use than
>> Blitz. Thing I like about Blitz most is the user has the choice
>> of exaclty HOW they want to code, using internal Window library
>> which is slower and creates bigger exe`s. Or do it completely with
>> the OS which would produce damn small EXE. Or even inbetween
>> and use the NLibs. (PB seems like the nlibs, a sort of inbetween.)
> 
>  Nlibs use OS calls-  I don't think you could make the Nlib calls
> smaller by any relevent degree. And aren't Nlibs just direct
> replacements for the Blitz commands?

I didn`t mean that, what I meant was that he`s done it with the same
amount of work you have to do to use the NLibs in Blitz. IE it`s
inbetween Blitz and C, nlibs take care of objects but leave tags
and stuff upto you, whereas in C yo do it all, and in blitz, Blitz manages
EVERYTHING, which I think is the way a BASIC language should be written.

Like I say, thats why I like Blitz, because if you want, you can use it
as BASIC, and have blitz do everything for you, or you can get as
complicated as C. It`s upto the programmer.

Cya.

-- 

Rob,
-- 
