[=>> about.. Thats as random as
[=>> it gets... So the seed is determined from the timer,
[=>> and numbers after
[=>> it are random.. Viola. :)
[=> 
[=> Probability and random are two different things. 100000 to 1 is
[=> unlikely, but I don't see how a value is randomly chosen? What is the
[=> timer compared to? And why did you say Viola? You're getting your wrods
[=> mixed up! ;)

Right the Timer count's how many ticks since the Amiga was turned on!  So
every time the miggy is powered up it will change the seed for RND!

Eg.

#Rnd# (?) Will always produce the same number when the program is started!

#Randomise timer# will never be the same value when you start the program
unless it is stared at exactly the same time every time you run the program!

My spelling maybe bad due to the quantity of beer I have just drank :)  But
I'm sure it's right.... Even though I'm P*ssed :).

Regards
-- 
