Hello Rob.

You wrote:

> This will take the initial random-seed of the miggy`s CIATimer..
> This is as "Random" as you`ll get it :) (I think)

Offcourse, Rnd is what is called "True Random", as opposed to the RRnd function that allows you to specify seeds, so that you will be able get the same string of random numbers each time you try. (Very usefull for generateing random levels and fractal landscapes. Worms anyone ?) :o>

Oh, also this function is allmost useless on autobooting software.

> [=> how my Miggy does random numbers? Surely computers are too stupid to

> It`s just a mathematical formula, basically, it has an inital number, then
> it performs a mathematical calculation on it to change it.. 
> This means that if you use Rnd or RRnd without RRandomize, the inital
> /Seed/ hasn`t changed, and everytime you run your program it will
> pick the numbers in exactly the same order.

Not true for the Rnd operation. It's a true random rutine and will return different values regardless of what seed you give RRandomize. Offcourse it's still a progressive iteration random number generator.


