On 09-Jul-99, Rob Hutchinson flashed:

>Or is it? ehehe
>Notice how 100 never gets picked.. EXACLTY like RRnd.. Never picking the
>top number..

  That is the way all random functions work AFAIK.  You simply must always
add 1 to the result to get the exact range you were after.  Eg:

  dwell=Int(Rnd(32))+1

Will insert a whole number between 1 and 32 inclusive into the variable
"dwell" each time it is run.



Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



