@NODE "Mail_467" "RIPack library question"
From: "Krzysztof Jonko" <eteacher@amiga.org.pl>
Subject: RIPack library question
Date: Tue, 6 Jul 1999 21:25:21 +0200
	charset="iso-8859-2"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 9a7acfadb2dd40e6b25839ec0c733f57

I've found old library RIpackLib - there is an interesting for me
instruction
UnpackIFF.
If I good understood documentation this function SHOULD unpack stored in
memory IFF picture to desired bitmap, so I've loaded picture to the
allocated memory area and tried to "unpack" and... nothing happend. What I'm
doing wrong? I would like to use this command to unpack pictures stored in
one big file achieved by Seek instruction.

Chris, eteacher@amiga.org.pl




