> UnpackIFF.
> If I good understood documentation this function SHOULD unpack stored in
> memory IFF picture to desired bitmap, so I've loaded picture to the
> allocated memory area and tried to "unpack" and... nothing happend. What I'm
> doing wrong? I would like to use this command to unpack pictures stored in
> one big file achieved by Seek instruction.
> 
> Chris, eteacher@amiga.org.pl

Hi all,

if I remember, you're right : UnpackIFF allows you to decompress an IFF
image previously loaded in memory. I don't know how to use this, but I
think I have a source somewhere. In my opinion, it's a good way to
display an IFF picture, instead of load & show directly in a bitmap,
when you want to wait before to see this picture an save memory (picture
stays compressed in memory).

I will have a look,

Cheers,

			Mathias

