@NODE "Mail_469" "Re: RIPack library question"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Wed, 7 Jul 1999 09:36:48 +0100
Subject: Re: RIPack library question
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 35c62a461c255903063ba82ca4b5bbd5



Hi Chris,

> > 
> > I've found old library RIpackLib - there is an interesting for me
> > instruction
> > UnpackIFF.
> > If I good understood documentation this function SHOULD unpack stored in
> > memory IFF picture to desired bitmap, so I've loaded picture to the
> > allocated memory area and tried to "unpack" and... nothing happend. What
> > I'm doing wrong? I would like to use this command to unpack pictures
> > stored in one big file achieved by Seek instruction.

I tried it last night, with the program at the end of the message. It worked 
OK. You need to make sure that the bitmap is big enough (width, height and 
depth) to hold the IFF, or the IFF will not be unpacked. Try printing the 
return value from UnpackIFF and see what it is. It may be a problem with your 
loading into memory as well, because if the routine can not find an IFF picture 
at the specified address, it will also abort. You will need to make sure that 
the whole of the file is loaded into the memory, as I did below.


; ------------------------------
a$="work:simpsons.iff"
ILBMInfo a$
BitMap 0,ILBMWidth,ILBMHeight,ILBMDepth
If ReadFile(0,a$)
    x.l = Lof(0)
   ; Can't rememeber the numbers for these constants, use amigalibs.res
    bmp.l = AllocMem(x,#MEMF_ANY|#MEMF_CLEAR)
    If bmp Then ReadMem 0,bmp,x
    CloseFile 0
End If

If bmp
    If UnpackIFF(bmp,0)
        WBToScreen 0
        Window 0,0,0,640,400,$100f,"jfj",-1,-1
        BitMapToWindow 0,0
        While WaitEvent<>$200:WEnd
    End If
    FreeMem bmp,x
End If

End

-- 
|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| © |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
