@NODE "Mail_476" "Run from Execute_"
From: "Neil Bullock" <trogladite@trogsoft.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Run from Execute_
Date: Wed, 21 Jul 1999 13:25:53 +0100
Organization: Trogladite Software
	charset="Windows-1252"
Encoding: 7bit
X-Info: Selby College, England
X-UIDL: 7e612249edaefa7088d5e1c0b7adbe17

Hi,

I'm attempting to get the Run command to work from the Execute_ Function in
Blitz.

e=Execute_("Run program >nil:",0,0)

Except that that doesn't work with various programs. There doesn't seem to be
a pattern between the ones that it doesn't work with, it just doesn't work. If
I remove the '>nil:' part, a window opens with '[CLI X]' (X being the process
number) in it, which is something I want to surpress.

How can I go about executing a program using Run, but not get output? Or,
alternatively (which is why I'm using Run in the first place) how can I get to
run a program to it returns to the Blitz program which launched it rather than
waiting for the program to return?

Thanks
Neil

