Hello Rob.

You wrote:

> Does it just work by copying a small section of data from fastmem
> into a small buffer in chipmem, and then syncing it perfectly so that
> it`s being rewritten while it`s playing? Or is it ACTUALLY playing from
> fastmem? (BTW - I`m talking about things like AHI and OSS here :))

Offcourse it isn't actually playing from fastram, the AMiGA chipset can only access chipram, so yes, you do copy it to chip, one piece at a time.

If you have a sound card hoever, you might be able to play it from fast, depends on what card you have.

> And finally, is there anything that can be used in blitz to achieve this?
> And I`m not talking about AHI or OSS mods.. I mean raw asm routines :)
