@NODE "Mail_480" "Re: Screen Events"
From: "Vic E Babes" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Screen Events
Date: Sat, 3 Jul 1999 13:01:02 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 29ad26d48743198363e5de6759c4c81c

> I have a HD, but F all space on it. I've had trouble putting stuff on
> floppies: at places the game freezes, and the orange LED is on
> permenantly.

The orange LED is probably on all the time because the program didn`t wait
for disk activity to finish - the manual recommends putting a delay_ 150
before going into Blitz mode, as there is no way to detect that disk
activity has finished.  If developing on a HD, you probably won`t notice
this problem with floppy access.

VIC



