@NODE "Mail_483" "Re: Screen Tags"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 5 Jul 1999 13:48:22 +0100
Subject: Re: Screen Tags
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 46b525875f8528a9654c8a16fbb955f6



> What is the screen tag for opening an interlaced screen? Also where can I
> find a list of all the screen tags? I think I may have asked this before
> but I don't remember what the answer was.

Probably #SA_DisplayID, you'd also need to specify 4 for interlaced, as well as 
any other information (i.e. hires etc). Pal would be $21000 | 4 | (hires 
anything else) NTSC would be $11000 | 4 | (hires etc here).

Screen tags would be in the OpenScreen function in the intution autodoc 
(http://www.redrobe.demon.co.uk). Probably also useful to get a set of OS 
includes as well.


