@NODE "Mail_485" "Re: screenmode type question"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Fri, 30 Jul 1999 09:47:24 +0100
Subject: Re: screenmode type question
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: cc3af65e662c537596cc90d66e5e2b78



> Hello,
> 
> Just a small niggle.
> 
> What would be the difference between,
> 
> PAL Hires Lace - on an SVGA with Scandoubler & Flickerfixer
> 
> and a
> 
> DBLPAL Hires on SVGA with SD but without FF  
> 
> both 640*512,256 col screens 
> 
> would they display as same or would on be more steady?
> 
> which?

PAL Hires Lace with SD/FF will be quite stable. Is your DBLPAL Hires screenmode 
"Laced" or "No Flicker"? If its no flicker then that'll probably be more 
stable. If its laced then it'll be laced and make you go blind without the FF.


