On 30-Jul-99, Mike Child wrote:

> 
>>> What would be the difference between,
>>> 
>>> PAL Hires Lace - on an SVGA with Scandoubler & Flickerfixer
>>> 
>>> and a
>>> 
>>> DBLPAL Hires on SVGA with SD but without FF
>>> 
>>> both 640*512,256 col screens
>>> 
>> 
>> PAL Hires Lace with SD/FF will be quite stable. Is your DBLPAL Hires
>> screenmode "Laced" or "No Flicker"? If its no flicker then that'll probably
>> be more stable. If its laced then it'll be laced and make you go blind
>> without the FF.
> 
> Couple more points - PAL Hires lace is a 15khz mode, artificially 
> doubled up by the scan doubler - wheras Double Pal is (can't remember 
> exactly) more like 30khz. This means the computer is doing more work 
> for Double Pal and the display redraws slower.
> 

The main reason for asking was to determine if I should get a ScanDoubler or 
ScanDoubler with FlickerFixer, I think the FF would be an advantage because I
do use hires lace quite a bit, and it seems the added workload for a DBLPAL
would slow down the system.

Until I get a GFX card, that is.

Thanks.

Leigh
