@NODE "Mail_496" "Re: Silly Question"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Wed, 07 Jul 1999 08:33:32 +0500
Subject: Re: Silly Question
X-UIDL: 08119871543103173b11c20dcb41f391

On 04-Jul-99, Tony Rolfe flashed:
>Donovan mentioned, the other day, that the Boxer will remove the 2Mb
>Chip ram limitation.   Since it will also have a built-in
>flicker-fixed and scan-doubler, will there be any point in getting a
>graphics board as well as a boxer?


   The removal of the chip-ram limitation will greatly improve certain
aspects of Amiga useage, especially multitasking with large AGA screens
and useage of large soundfiles with the Amiga built-in sound functions.

  It will however not increase the capabilities of the AGA chipset to
address larger screenmodes (a chipset speed issue), therefor, the
addition of a graphics card to the mix is still desireable for some
applications.


cacha later,

Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



