Subject: Slider problems
X-UIDL: 63308183929591ea6fc5496d422110cc

Hello,

In my application I am trying to have three sliders and three integer
gadgets, connected in such a way that if you move a slider, the integer
will change and vice versa. Changing the integer gadget does have the right
effect, but when you change the slider, the integer gets reset to 0. I
can't figure out, what I am doing wrong, so I am sending here the relevant
code:

  ...

  GTSlider 0,5,150,25,10,65,"R",#PLACETEXT_ABOVE+$400,-100,100
  ...
  GTInteger 0,8,250,35,45,12,"Red",#PLACETEXT_LEFT,dRed

  ...

  Repeat
    If WaitEvent=#IDCMP_GADGETUP
      Select GadgetHit

        ...

        Case 5  ; doesn't work
          dRed=GTGetAttrs(0,5,#GTSL_Level)
          GTSetInteger 0,8,dRed
        ...
        Case 8  ; works fine
          dRed=GTGetInteger(0,8)
          GTSetAttrs 0,5,#GTSL_Level,dRed

        ...

      End Select
    EndIf
  Until EndSet.b=True


Kind regards
-- 
