@NODE "Mail_505" "Re: Slider problems"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 21 Jul 1999 17:25:28 -0500
Subject: Re: Slider problems
X-UIDL: cdd4ee7fb62410bf88d516a954de2ce1

--BOUNDARY.1748476576.1

Hi Damir

On 21-Jul-99, Damir Arh wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> In my application I am trying to have three sliders and three integer
> gadgets, connected in such a way that if you move a slider, the integer
> will change and vice versa. Changing the integer gadget does have the
> right effect, but when you change the slider, the integer gets reset to 0.
> I can't figure out, what I am doing wrong, so I am sending here the
> relevant code:

I've attached a piece of code that might help.  It was snipped from a
program. so some of the variables may not make sense.  Also, I am only
using text gadgets for the display, but the same method should work for
your integer gadgets.

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748476576.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="slider.asc"

WBenchToFront_
WbToScreen 0

; -- Gadget ID numbers: --

#widthview = 50
#heightview =51
#yes =52
#no = 53
#xpsize = 54

; -- Just some stuff patched in to replace the whole rest of the program -
;    don't worry about 'em

xpx.w=320
xpy.w=200
win_width=320
Xmax=900
winscale=xpy/xpx


; -- The GTGadgetList

GTTags #GTTX_Justification,#GTJ_CENTER,#GTNM_Clipped,True
GTText   4,#widthview,66,46,65,23,"Width",#PLACETEXT_BELOW,Str$(xpx)

GTTags #GTTX_Justification,#GTJ_CENTER,#GTNM_Clipped,True
GTText   4,#heightview,226,46,65,23,"Height",#PLACETEXT_BELOW,Str$(xpy)

GTButton 4,#yes,26,118,126,16,"OK",$80|#PLACETEXT_IN

GTButton 4,#no,204,118,126,16,"Cancel",$80|#PLACETEXT_IN

GTSlider 4,#xpsize,26,89,304,16,"",$80|8,win_width,Xmax
GTSetAttrs 4,#xpsize,#GTSL_Level,xpx

AddIDCMP $20|$10   ;-- for immediate output from the slider ----

; -- finally, a window opens! --

Window 4,138,130,364,158,$1000,"Buffer Export",1,2
offx.b = WLeftOff
AttachGTList 4,4
WLocate 50,26
Print"Set the size for the iff picture:"

gd=0

Repeat
  ev.l=WaitEvent
    If ev=$20          ;a gadget is pressed down
      gd=GadgetHit

      If gd=#xpsize    ;read the slider
        Repeat         ;and keep updating
          ev.l=Event   ;as long as it is held down
          xpx=EventCode
          xpy=xpx*winscale
          VWait
          GTSetAttrs 4,#widthview,#GTTX_Text,Str$(xpx)
          VWait
          GTSetAttrs 4,#heightview,#GTTX_Text,Str$(xpy)
        Until ev=$40   ;gadget released
      EndIf

    EndIf

Until gd=#yes OR gd=#no


End


--BOUNDARY.1748476576.1

