@NODE "Mail_508" "Spot the Enforcer hit"
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 20 Jul 1999 03:19:12 +0100
Subject: Spot the Enforcer hit
X-UIDL: f8100df5e1fef1c68ebac3013151c15e

--BOUNDARY.1747970752.2

Hi all, 

I'm writing a little hack to let me resize another program's window
(for nasty programs that don't save their position - I can call this
along with whatever program from ToolsDaemon, y'see :)

It works fine, but can anyone tell why it should cause an Enforcer hit
if no window exists with the user's chosen title? I've narrowed it down
to the line which compares the current window's title with what the user
wants (see .BUG), but I don't see what the actual problem is :/

Compile it, and call it like this (called WinShift for now) :

  WinShift title x y width height delay

title is the title of the window to be moved, x is the, uh x-position,
ditto for y, width and height are thenew window dimensions (use zero
to keep the same) and delay is the number of seconds to wait before
doing the "shift" (you can specify 0)...

I'm gonna add support for other screens (well, maybe...only for windows
on the WB screen right now), and less strict window title recognition,
but I'd like to lose the hit for now ;)

Thanks :)
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. 
<sb>(http://surf.to/all-hail/)
<tsb>

The only way to get rid of a temptation is to yield to it.
-- Oscar Wilde

--BOUNDARY.1747970752.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="WinHack.asc"
Content-Description: Program to move/size another's window on the WB.

; WinShift - a hack to reposition another program's window

; Hackware in the Public Domain by James L Boyd
; (jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk)

; --------------------------------------------------------

; It's called from CLI, like this :

;   WinShift "Test Window" 0 11 0 0 1

; This moves window with title of "Test Window" to position
; 0,11 and keeps it the same size (that's what 0 0 does here),
; after waiting for one second.

; Parameters are : window title, x position, y position, width,
; height and delay in seconds.

; --------------------------------------------------------

; CLI-only replacement for Nprint :

Statement Prt {text$}
  text$+Chr$(10)+Chr$(0)
  PutStr_ &text$
End Statement

; Error message when number of CLI parameters isn't 6 :

If NumPars<>6
  Prt {""}
  Prt {"WinShift < window x y width height seconds >"}
  Prt {""}
  Prt {"James L Boyd 1999 - Public Domain Hackware :)"}
  Prt {""}
  Prt {"eg. WinShift "+Chr$(34)+"MCDPlayer V1.01"+Chr$(34)+" 50 50 0 0 2"}
  Prt {""}
  Prt {"This would move the MCDP window to x=50 and y=50,"}
  Prt {"keeping the window's original size, waiting for 2 seconds"}
  Prt {""}
  Prt {"See docs for more details"}
  End
EndIf

; read CLI parameters :

w$=Par$(1)
x.w=Val(Par$(2))
y.w=Val(Par$(3))
width.w=Val(Par$(4))
height.w=Val(Par$(5))
del.b=Val(Par$(6))

  wb$="Workbench"                     ; Note : only for WB windows here!
  *scr.Screen = LockPubScreen_ (&wb$) ; lock the Workbench screen

  winlist                             ; window checking routine
  *win.Window = *scr\FirstWindow      ; get screen's first window

  While *win                                    ; got one?
      If width=0 Then width=*win\Width          ; check width parameter
      If height=0 Then height=*win\Height       ; check height parameter

.BUG ; Enforcer hit here if there's no window with title w$ :

      If Peek$(*win\Title)=w$ Then Goto popout  ; got it? go shift it!

      *win = *win\NextWindow                    ; nope, check next one
  Wend

  UnlockPubScreen_ &wb$,*scr                    ; free the Workbench screen
  End                                           ; didn't find window

  popout                                        ; go here when window's found

  UnlockPubScreen_ &wb$,*scr                    ; free the Workbench screen

  If del Then Delay_ del*50
  ChangeWindowBox_ *win,x,y,width,height        ; shift it!

End                                             ; End...duh...


--BOUNDARY.1747970752.2

---------------------------------------------------------------------
