For additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie
--BOUNDARY.1747970752.2--




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_509" "Re: Spot the Enforcer hit"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 19 Jul 1999 18:45:54 -0500
Subject: Re: Spot the Enforcer hit
X-UIDL: 643ad28f8034e3997eab22c12e57e1dd

--BOUNDARY.1748292968.3

Hi James

On 19-Jul-99, James L Boyd wrote:

> It works fine, but can anyone tell why it should cause an Enforcer hit
> if no window exists with the user's chosen title? I've narrowed it down
> to the line which compares the current window's title with what the user
> wants (see .BUG), but I don't see what the actual problem is :/

The actual problem is not that it isn't finding a matching title - the real
problem is that there can be some windows with no title (ie, "") lurking
about. 
In that case, the pointer to the title will be 0, so you are trying to peek
a string from location 0, getting an enforcer hit for your troubles.

Try substituting the attached bit of code.  No more Enforcer hits here!

Later...
-- 


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748292968.3
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="Fix.asc"

.BUG ; Enforcer hit here if there's no window with title w$ :
        If *win\Title
          check$=Peek$(*win\Title)
        Else
          check$="window with no title!"
        EndIf
        NPrint check$
        If check$=w$ Then Goto popout  ; got it? go shift it!
        *win = *win\NextWindow                    ; nope, check next one


--BOUNDARY.1748292968.3

