To unsubscribe, e-mail: blitz-list-unsubscribe@netsoc.ucd.ie
For additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie
--BOUNDARY.1748292968.3--




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_510" "Talk2Me"
From: "Vic E Babes" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Talk2Me
Date: Mon, 12 Jul 1999 17:55:09 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: db80dea9b8027d922cbf90937adb720e

Just a quick note for those that I sent copies of Talk2Me (speech GUI).

Curt has pointed out to me that it doesn`t open a screen of the right size
on an NTSC machine, which I`ve corrected.  I also stated in the guide that
the "Manual" option was not available because altering the translated string
would change its length, and I didn`t know how blitz informed the
narrator.device of the string`s length - but Curt reminded me about the
command "PhoneticSpeack" - so I have now added the Manual feature, and have
enabled editing of the translated string.

Thanks for that, Curt.

I am also removing the menu, and the Load/Save buttons, in favour of a
pop-up menu that appears under the mouse on a RMB press.  Should be ready in
a few days, after further testing, but can`t remember everyone that asked
for it, so if you want the new version - let me know.

VIC
zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk



