@NODE "Mail_511" "tester(s) wanted"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 29 Jul 1999 13:18:59 -0500
Subject: tester(s) wanted
X-UIDL: 1c503de24128c937fa13757c7cfe2619

Hi everyone,

I have a small utility ready for uploading to Aminet.  But I would like to
have it tested on some other systems to be sure it works.  What it does is
to grab the Amiga's speech output and save it as a standard iff or wav
sample file.

You will need to have a working speech setup on your system, including the
original cli-Say command (usually found in SYS:utilities/)

Any volunteers?  Email me privately for the archive (34k lzx) 

Later...


