@NODE "Mail_543" "Re: This is frying my brain!"
Date: Sun, 4 Jul 1999 23:11:24 +0100 (BST)
From: =?iso-8859-1?q?Ayar=20Baboon?= <compiler_monkey@yahoo.co.uk>
Subject: Re: This is frying my brain!
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 6c269e649a115493966304b306dc1a9f


>    I've attached the complete menu code for ym
> RDogzII game. Howver,
> it don't BBlit the shapes onto the options menu. Can
> some1 take a look
> at the code and atempt to find out why please.

Without looking at the code, one problem I came across was the way I
was drawing stuff. Perhaps you're wiping the graphics as soon as
they're drawn. The way it should be:

Repeat
	Vwait
	Unbuffer
	Draw all the graphics
Until whenever.

Also, you're probably doing double buffering? Then it could be a case
of you showing the wrong bitmap? Or if you're not double buffering,
perhaps that's why (are the shapes big 'buttons'?)

Also you could be 'using' the wrong bitmap or buffer.

> Also, how do I make the mouse movement less
> sluggish?

Are u using the mouse pointer or blitting a shape to the mousie's
coordinates?

Bye
	James

