Hi Ayar

On 04-Jul-99, Ayar Baboon wrote:

>> Then I start work on the HiScores table (oh god! I
>> dunno how to dot
>> that! I might just attempt to convert some AMOS code
>> over :)
> 
> Ah, I'm looking to do this myself. Are you going to have a NewType for
> a table entry? I've done a high score system before, but I cheated by
> having only three entries per table (lots easier to code!)
> If you're seriously going to use Amos code, can I have a look?
> I have the extra worry of recording the player's time.

I did the score table for my game by putting each bit of information into an
array (names, times played, times won, etc...)

Then it's easy to compare or sort the whole thing on any of the variables
you like - you can look for the same player name, for example, or sort by
the best time, highest score, or whatever.  I sort mine on the total number
of games played, then on the games won.

You could use a newtype, or standard arrays if you prefer...

I cheated a bit by stuffing the entire thing into a GTlistview, so you get
everybody's scores, no matter how badly they have done (one of the
advantages of using Amiga mode) but it's easy to chop it down to a "top
ten" or less and print it out on the screen.


Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



