@NODE "Mail_563" "Transloucency In Mildred"
From: Jake Frederick <gonzo@acadia.net>
Date: Mon, 05 Jul 1999 14:27:35 +0500
Subject: Transloucency In Mildred
X-UIDL: e4741a3fbc61757e0c7ddabe94e448bc

--BOUNDARY.26614640.1

Attached is a small section of code that I'm using for a transloucent shadow
effect. I have a 32 bit half bright palette set up with 16 colors for the
ground and 16 darker shades for the shadow. Does anyone know a quicker way to
do this in Mildred? 
-- 
-If the doors of perception were cleansed everything would appear to man as it
truly is, infinite.-

--BOUNDARY.26614640.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="shadow"

shadowx=0
shadowy=0
MUseShape shadow
Repeat
  If MPointCookie(shadowx,shadowy,shadow)=-1
    color=MPoint(x+shadowx,y+shadowy,1)
    MPlotShape shadowx,shadowy,color+16
  End If
  shadowx+1
  If shadowx=50 Then shadowx=0:shadowy+1
Until shadowy=50



--BOUNDARY.26614640.1

