Hi Jake

On 05-Jul-99, Jake Frederick wrote:
> Attached is a small section of code that I'm using for a transloucent shadow
> effect. I have a 32 bit half bright palette set up with 16 colors for the
> ground and 16 darker shades for the shadow. Does anyone know a quicker way
> do this in Mildred? 

Yep, it's a piece 'a piss it really is :)
Just use the table commands and the mqblitmode remapmode (or whatever blit)

Ive made a utility which loads in a palette and can make 2D remap tables for
use in Mildred, i made this ages ago :) i haven't released it yet because
it needs to font sensative (as Paul West pointed out), needs to support 1D,
And i havn't been arsed doing any docs for it :)

Ive been too bussy with my game to do any new utilities like CNKI for Mildred.

As with collision detection in Mildred, this is dead easy as well, all you
have to do is compare the 2 cookies of the shapes then do a logical AND on the
2 bytes and if the 2 bytes are -1 then you have a collision!

Ive already done a routine in normal blitz code like a BlitColl command, its
pretty fast but ill be making some propper routines in ASM over the next
couple of weeks.

If u really need transluency i can always send you the RemapTableGenarator
now, but it isn't finnished.

Im using it already in my game, Paul did a great job with Mildred :)

Hope that helps ;)

Chris.
