On 05-Jul-99, Anton Reinauer wrote.

>    Rick has said most of the important points already; AMarquee uses
>  TCP, which can be up to 10 times slower than UDP in lag times, that's
>  why I wrote my UDPFuncs, so you can write fast action net multiplayer
>  games. The other reason I didn't bother with it, is that you're relying
>  on someone else to for your multiplayer connection- what if the
>  programmer decides to go to the PC, and won't bother fixing a bug, or
>  won't update the code for OS5- then you're screwed!
>    Anyway, it's easier to use my routines than Amarquee anyway, you only
>  need TCP-to-Blitz.lha from dev/basic on Aminet, and recompile your
>  Deflibs with bsdsocket.library1 in your amigalibs drawer in Blitzlibs: .
>  Hardly difficult (and you'd have to do that for the AMarquee lib
>  anyhow). All the login/disconnect code in my UDP_Funcs is already done,
>  and is virtually transparent to the program, with Amarquee you'd have
>  to do all the library calls to the lib, which would take much more work
>  than using my Funcs! 

Well how about making those functions as a library? It would then be easy
to convert that to PB!

Of course it would be better to finish those functions before turning it in
to a library, so that the translation would be as bug free as it possibly
can.
And the translator would only need to bother from the bugs he/she made
while converting it.

