@NODE "Mail_576" "Re: Using rastport"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 11 Jul 1999 09:58:28 -0500
Subject: Re: Using rastport
X-UIDL: f573c93577d0c884452a9cdf513be34b

Hi Damir

On 11-Jul-99, Damir Arh wrote:
> Hello everyone
> 
> On 11-Jul-99, Curt Esser shared his opinion:

> 
>>> Hey Curt, would you mind sending me a copy of that?
> 
>> I'll just post it on the list for everybody - it's small.
> 
> Thank you very much. I could find good use for this function. I already
> adapted it a bit to check, whether the text fits on the bitmap or not. But
> there is one problem, I still have. Is there any known problem with the
> style parameter of the LoadFont command. I tried setting it to every
> possible value, but the font still gets printed in normal style. Is there
> something I am missing?

The "Style" setting in the LoadFont command does nothing - I think it is
left over from 1.3.  It is easy to change the style in a window, using the
second parameter of the WindowFont command.

For example "WindowFont 0,4" will make the text in this window use font 0,
italic.

For the BitMap printing function, there must be some setting in the RastPort
for this, but I don't know how.

-- 


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



