@NODE "Mail_594" "Re: Which GFX-Card"
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Thu, 08 Jul 1999 23:26:39 +1200
Subject: Re: Which GFX-Card
X-UIDL: 1440faa2c408e250f2981b25d4192547

On 08-Jul-99, Leigh Parry wrote:
> Hello, sorry for being off topic.

> I'm shortly going to get a GFX Card, But Which is better for price?
> Any Help?

> AteoBus + Pixel64

> ZorroBus + Picasso 4

> Blizzard 603 + Blizzard Vision

 If you can afford it, the Blizzard option is best, as you're not slowed
down by Motherboard as the Graphics chips are connected direct to the
CPUs. It for example, speeds up QuakePPC, from 320*256 at 20 fps, to
640*480 at around 30 fps!! On the other boards, you probably won't get
any speed up, as the C2P copy through the motherboard will be the
same :-/

  The only problem, is it's a lot of money to spend, if the NG Amiga
comes out on time- ie: 1st quarter next year :-/  If they could
guarantee that OS5 will be on PPC, it wouldn't be so bad- at the moment
it's only a possibility!
 
-- 
        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
       


