@NODE "Mail_595" "Re: Which GFX-Card"
From: Jake Frederick <gonzo@acadia.net>
Date: Thu, 08 Jul 1999 18:00:57 +0500
Subject: Re: Which GFX-Card
X-UIDL: 766536879de266faf2e37fc5485fc4ad

On 08-Jul-99, Leigh Parry wrote:
> Hello, sorry for being off topic.
> 
> I'm shortly going to get a GFX Card, But Which is better for price? Any
Help?
> 
> AteoBus + Pixel64
> 
> ZorroBus + Picasso 4
> 
> Blizzard 603 + Blizzard Vision
> 
I was faced with the same decision and I got a Pixel 64. In retrospect I would
have bought the PPC/BlizzardVision because I ended up frying a motherboard
and Power Flyer trying to install it. If you have an Ateo tower it would
probably be easy to install though. If you have the money I'd get the Bvision
since it's faster, it's got 8 megs of Ram rather than 2 and it has a 3D chip.
A1200 Zorro buses are slow, unless you get Zorro III in which case they're
incredibly expensive and they require an A4000 accellerator.
-- 
