On 19-Jul-99, Neil Bullock Wrote........

[=> Ok, has anyone got any idea how to close a window when it's deselcted.
[=> The code I'm using at the moment is something like

Try this Neil ;).
Regards
-- 
<tsb>
*Email:*# Hawkeye@satanicdreams.in2home.co.uk #| *ICQ:*  #27181384#
*SDS FOUNDER:* #URL: http://www.satanicdreams.freeserve.co.uk/#
*PROJECT INFO:* #APU-MUI (AFS/PFS Undelete) #(92% complete.  Beta testers wanted)
_*PGP key available on request.*_

"Speaking as a man in the street... AAAUUUGGGHHH!"
<tsb>


--BOUNDARY.24331712.6
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="DeactivateWindow.Asc"


WBStartup
WbToScreen0
Window 0,0,0,200,100,$1|$2|$4|$8|$1000,"De-Activate test!",1,2
AddIDCMP $40000|$80000

Repeat
ev.l=WaitEvent
If ev=$80000 AND EventWindow=0 OR ev=$200
CloseWindow 0
End
EndIf
Until Joyb(0)=3
End


--BOUNDARY.24331712.6

