@NODE "Mail_604" "Re: Window Deselction"
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 21 Jul 1999 02:58:28 +0100
Subject: Re: Window Deselction
X-UIDL: 97e22cde41df9fb771cceb79321493f6

--BOUNDARY.1748289904.1

Neil Bullock churned out *this* drivel:

> <open window up here>
> 
> Repeat
>  W=WaitEvent
>  If W=$80000 AND EventWindow=1
>    CloseWindow 1
>  Endif
> Forever
> 
> Which doesn't work. Any ideas?

"W" should be a long value...and I added an End to my version,
otherwise you're stuck, but it depends what else you've got happening
obviously... 

See attached...

See ya,
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. 
<sb>(http://surf.to/all-hail/)
<tsb>

I'm not a member of any organized political party, I'm a Democrat!
-- Will Rogers

--BOUNDARY.1748289904.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="OutOfWindow.asc"
Content-Description: Click outside window to close

FindScreen 0

Window 1,0,0,640,100,$20140f,"",1,2

Repeat

  W.l=WaitEvent

  If EventWindow=1

    If W=$80000

      CloseWindow 1
      End

    EndIf

  EndIf

Forever



--BOUNDARY.1748289904.1

